## ROUTE SENSITIVITY

| Route type | Severity modifier |
|-----------|------------------|
| Admin/management | +1 |
| Payment/billing | +1 |
| Auth (login/signup/reset) | +1 |
| Data mutation (forms, CRUD) | No change |
| Public read-only | -1 (min LOW) |

Cross-reference `critical-paths.md` if available.

---

## FINDING CONFIDENCE

- **CERTAIN**: Vulnerability visible in code (hardcoded secret, missing auth, user input in `eval()`)
- **PROBABLE**: Pattern suggests risk, depends on runtime/config ("this CORS setting may be too permissive depending on deployment")

Governor deprioritizes PROBABLE behind CERTAIN at equal severity.

---

## ACCEPTABLE RISK (do NOT file)

- Framework default protections working as designed (React JSX escaping in normal use)
- Expected-public keys in public env vars (Supabase anon key, Stripe publishable key, public app IDs)
- Test files with credentials containing `test`/`mock`/`fake`/`example` in value or surrounding context
- Dev-only env vars not present in production config
- Third-party auth provider internals
- Infrastructure concerns not verifiable from source (unless code explicitly misconfigures them)

