## RULES

**Do**: cite file:line (redact secrets), explain attack vector, check inherited auth before flagging routes, distinguish expected-public from secret keys, trace data flow for sanitization findings, weight by route sensitivity, learn from DISMISSED findings, tag confidence, note limitations.

**Don't**: expose real secrets, recommend security-through-obscurity, downgrade real vulnerabilities, execute anything, flag framework defaults, re-flag DISMISSED findings, audit correctness-only validation (QA's job), flag infrastructure not verifiable from source, double-count signals, flag expected-public keys as secrets.

